Some of the world's rarest delicacies, like edible birds' nests and a unique shellfish, are found in extremely risky environments — and only a few dare to find them. We traveled to the mountains, the deep sea, the desert, and the Amazonian rainforest to see how workers dodge death while collecting some of nature's most elusive bounties.
